rComments:
Well, it is true that the lecture slides might a little bit messy but the exam was not that difficult if you understand well in lab and lecture.
However, it is really worth noting that the professor himself is nice and replied to emails and questions very friendly and responsible!

This prof knows how to get the material across to his students but to better understand his lecture slides (very unorganized) you have to show up to the lectures. Otherwise, the tests and labs were very straightforward with the instructions. This prof is ok.
The exam and tests are pretty easy if you attend class and pay attention. The labs were quite a challenge though, especially since it's online

Prof. Groza is excellent. All the bad reviews seem to be people who did not understand the course material, but you cannot expect to just show up to the lectures and understand everything right away. You must do some studying and reading on your own to do well in the class. He is exactly what he should be!

Prof Groza is a very passionate about computer architecture. Throughout the course, he would mention how what we're learning is used in later courses and systems. He generously only took our two highest tests out of four for that portion of the course and made the final exam very similar to the practice/old exams.
His lecture slides are definitely is overwhelming but once you understand the material, it is really good for looking back and refreshing on the steps for solving problems.

He seems like a nice enough guy that cares about his students. However, his lecture slides are a mess and almost impossible to follow. With the labs being online they were a complete mess and extremely frustrating. He also doesn't list expected test dates and will often give less than a week's notice before the tests which is rather annoying.

Groza is a very accomidating and nice professor, his quizzes take the easiest applications of the course concepts. Lectures slides are super disorganized though and on pretty much every practice test there was a typo or wrong answer, but he seemed to be one of the only profs who gave practice tests, labs are also hard but he gives you lots of time

Nice guy. Shows he cares about the students. His slides however, are such a mess and he can't see to explain things well. He is clearly knowledgeable but can't convey anything. Homework and midterm/final preparation is easy, but the midterm and final themselves were way harder. Had to memorize how to solve q's rather than understanding the concepts

Lectures were useless. Midterm and Final were hard. The labs were disorganized with TAs that were there just to make sure you did work. It's pointless to ask them for any help because they don't anything.

He's okay. Lectures will put you to sleep and the notes are a convoluted mess. Midterm isn't too hard as it resembles previous years and much of the material is from Digital Systems. The final exams of past years weren't too bad but ours was really really hard for some reason. Strongly advise reading the textbook to prep for the final exam.

Once you grow accustomed to his thick accent, his lectures become engaging and humourous. He explains the subject matter in a thorough manner. His slides are extremely helpful; they explain everything step by step, so you don't need the textbook. He posts problem sets with complete solutions. His style is best suited for "neurodivergent" students.

He should have become a chef, comparing potatoes or as he says "pataitoes" :) to a circuit board. I don't recall understanding lectures, getting the labs done with my friends without the help of the TAs, and reviewing the notes and slides and getting an A-. This guy has been teaching this course for over 15 years, so he too must be bored by now :).

His lectures are really hard to understand and he gets distracted very easily. I never went to lectures and just read the textbook. His midterm was super easy but the final was pretty hard. I wouldn't recommend taking him, he'll put you to sleep.

Lectures kinda sucked but whatever, Groza is a funny guy. DGDs were more helpful to pass the tests, make sure to attend those or review the problems on your own. Midterm and final were challenging but fair. The labs were cool but ruined by useless TAs.

Not at all good at conveying the course material. He knows his stuff but have a hard time explaining it to students, that being said if you go to his office he will take good amount of time to explain you stuff that you have problem in. Make sure to go to attend and learn in DGD's because you wont learn a lot in class. Exams- Fair.
Lectures and slides are a mess, but the class is an easy pass. Groza is the goat

Groza is a good professor. The real thing that will ruin this course for you are the terrible TAs and labs. They are disorganized, impatient, and worse of all: the lab schedule makes no sense. The labs will be on stuff no one has learned, and the TAs will only get mad if you ask for help. DGDs last for 10 minutes and are useless. Good luck.

I've had him for 2 courses, Comp arch 1&2. He is one of the worst at giving lectures just from the way he talks. He clearly likes the material and tries his best to give good lectures, but at the end of the day I fell asleep more often then not. But he is one of the nicest guys and a very gentle marker.

Nice professor, very helpful and extremely friendly.. recommend his course, assignments and exams are exactly what he teaches. You may find slides confusing if you would not listen in class, but concepts can easily be understood from next guy who concentrates iin lectures. Easy marker, easy on presentations and project.
Have no idea what he talks about.

Groza is a hit or miss. If you have prime interest in the subject, he'll convey the subject in his little nerdish manner. However, for me at least, the slides are extremely confusing and doesn't help when you can't stay awake in his class because you have no idea what's going on.

Extremely helpful and kind-hearted professor that' for sure. But this alone is not helpful enough. He always makes you (or atleast me) fall asleep in class even though I have 2 cups of strong coffee before his class. There is no other prof but this one that had made fall asleep ever in a lecture and I think its cause he goes on in too much detail.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Gives good feedback', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: He is the best professor in the computer engineering. very helpful and always care about his student.  Again I am very delightful to have him as my computer engineering professor/director.

Excellent Excellent Professor. Work load is high in his course and projects are tough. Even though he is a great professor and great gentleman. You can discuss problems with him, he always ready to find solution.

Not the best lecturer around as he tends to go off on tangents which serves primarily as source of confusion. The slides have many mistakes and apparently haven't been corrected in years. He is however a generous marker, and very helpful individually. There are few surprises on the exam, midterm or quizzes.
Very nice guy. But please don't follow his slides. His teaching is good. But teaches most unwanted stuff. Overall I would say, take his subjects.

A really nice guy full of good intents; however his slides are the most overloaded ones.  Seems to have issues with large group (tends to get angry when people talks) but my group was abnormaly large.  The subject needs to be studied if you don't know it.  He will explain it, but in his own very nerdish way talking about flying saucers. Concentrate

Nicest guy you'll ever have as a prof. However he is extremely difficult to follow during his lectures. Even with some prior knowledge on the subject matter, I had a hard time figuring out what he was trying to teach. Figuring out what he's going to test you on is the hardest challenge. Going to the tutorial is a good idea.
very eccentric.is not at all clear about what is going to be on the midterm and the final.its going to be hit and miss with him

Not exactly the most clear prof when it comes to his lectures... he has a very deranged sense of humour as well. However, everything in this course is do-able and his tests are fair. The course is not hard if you focus and study...
knowledgeable and nice prof. even he only gave me an A at last, i still think he is one of the best prof ~~ better pay more attention to his last lecture~ really helpful for final~
Teaching: absolutely terrible. Marking: Absolutely no way can be easier. Personality: Can't find anyone better. Easiness: Just do the problems, you will get full marks.
not prepared, boring class
The worst profs ever, never prepare his lecture. I got my first B mark from his class!!!! I am really really upset with it. Anyway, he is a nice guy.
excellent prof, I wish all profs are like him.
The Best prof in SITE. My Favorite Prof, i really like him and he's a really supper guy!

Okay, he's an old school guy. He was doing computer engineering for like 25 years. There's no complete notes for his classes, most of the valuable stuff is being taught from the head. I mean expect to THINK on his lectures. Probably one of the few PROFESSIONALS left in CEG program. Highly recommend.
Commerical breaks.. haha. Nice guy, good prof, gives you bumps in marks.
Well he's a nice prof, somehow easy exams,good marks, but i still think he used to work as a chef before (potatoes, sausages,...), but he's good , at least better than karmouch
One of the best profs in engineering. If you have the slightest sense of humor, you'll love him. Like they said, flying saucers, potatoes, our good book, and commercial breaks. Groza rules.
sausages, potatoes, our good book, what more do you want... best prof ever!
